# Optional direnv configuration for Koch Trainer
#
# Copy to .envrc and run `direnv allow` to enable.
# See: https://direnv.net/
#
# This file is optional. The default setup (beads in-repo) works without direnv.

# =============================================================================
# External Beads (Optional, Not Recommended)
# =============================================================================
# Use an external beads repo for complete separation from code history.
# Only use this if you specifically need beads commits separate from code.
#
# Setup:
#   mkdir -p ~/Coding/koch-trainer-beads
#   cd ~/Coding/koch-trainer-beads
#   git init
#   bd init --prefix koch
#
# Then uncomment:
# export BEADS_DIR="$HOME/Coding/koch-trainer-beads/.beads"

